---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Methodology · State of AI Code Review"
  description="How the data was produced. Source, filters, implementation status definition, privacy thresholds, reproducibility, and the selection-bias correction applied between drafts."
  runningHead="Methodology"
  page="Methodology"
>

  <section class="max-w-[1320px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pt-16 md:pt-20 pb-12">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-7">
        <h1 class="font-display leading-[0.98] tracking-tight text-ink-900 reveal reveal-1" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5rem);">
          How the <span class="italic">data was produced.</span>
        </h1>
      </div>
      <aside class="col-span-12 md:col-span-5 md:pt-8 reveal reveal-3">
        <div class="border-l border-ink-900 pl-5">
          <p class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.6] text-[15px]">
            This section documents the dataset, filtering criteria, the definition of "implementation status," privacy thresholds, and the selection-bias correction that altered our acceptance numbers between internal drafts and publication.
          </p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SELECTION BIAS NOTE -->
  <section class="dark-section border-y-2 border-ink-900">
    <div class="max-w-[1320px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-16">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
          <div class="stamp text-ochre-300">A note on honesty</div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <p class="font-display italic text-paper-100 leading-[1.3]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.6vw, 2.5rem);">
            An earlier internal draft reported 94.7% acceptance. That was wrong.
          </p>
          <p class="text-paper-300 leading-[1.7] text-[16px] mt-5 max-w-3xl">
            The draft counted only suggestions that received explicit developer feedback (thumbs-up, thumbs-down, or detected implementation). That table is a selection-biased subset of suggestions where the developer engaged. Silent ignores were missing entirely. When the full population is queried from the post-PR diff, the real implementation rate is 17%, not 94.7%. This report uses the full population.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-[1320px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 pb-20">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-10 border-t-2 border-ink-900 pt-16">

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ i</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Source</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          Production code reviews from the Kodus pipeline.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.7] mt-5 max-w-prose">
          Kodus reviews pull requests across GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, and Azure DevOps. The full dataset lives in a BigQuery warehouse. Each chart in this report has a backing SQL query published in the <a href="https://github.com/kodustech/stateofcodereview.com" class="underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 hover:text-oxblood-500">GitHub repository</a> under <code class="font-mono text-sm bg-paper-200 px-1.5 py-0.5">methodology/queries/</code>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ ii</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Implementation status</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          Measured from the post-PR diff, not opt-in feedback.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.7] mt-5 max-w-prose">
          For every delivered suggestion, the pipeline compares the suggested code against what actually shipped on those lines after the PR closed. The status is one of three:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.75] mt-5 space-y-2 list-none max-w-prose">
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-moss-500">▣</span> <strong>implemented</strong> · the developer applied the suggested change closely.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-ochre-500">▦</span> <strong>partially_implemented</strong> · the developer changed those lines but not exactly as suggested. The idea was taken, the form was adapted.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">▢</span> <strong>not_implemented</strong> · the lines were left untouched, or the change went in a different direction.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.7] mt-5 max-w-prose">
          This is a behavioral measure, not a quality measure. A correct suggestion ignored because the developer disagreed is counted as "not implemented." A wrong suggestion the developer happened to also fix differently is counted "partially." We discuss this trade-off in chapter notes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ iii</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Engine cutoff</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          Suggestions before 2025-09-01 are excluded.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.7] mt-5 max-w-prose">
          Kodus introduced the current label taxonomy in September 2025 with five canonical labels (bug, security, performance, cross-file, kody rules). Earlier suggestions used a different label set and prompt and are excluded so findings remain interpretable as the current state.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ iv</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Privacy</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          Aggregation only.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.75] mt-5 space-y-2 list-none max-w-prose">
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">a.</span> No slice with fewer than 50 suggestions is published.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">b.</span> Language slices with fewer than three distinct organizations are footnoted as low-confidence.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">c.</span> Organization, repository, and pull-request identifiers are never exposed.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">d.</span> Suggestion text shown in the report is reviewed for sensitive substrings before publication.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ v</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Sample sizes</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          2026-Q2 snapshot.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-6 border-t border-ink-900">
          {[
            ['Delivered suggestions (sent, post-cutoff)', '112,336'],
            ['Distinct organizations', '456'],
            ['Fully implemented', '19,107 (17.0%)'],
            ['Partially implemented', '18,390 (16.4%)'],
            ['Ignored', '74,839 (66.6%)'],
            ['Bug-label findings', '90,527'],
            ['Security-label findings', '6,552'],
            ['Cross-file findings', '10,992'],
            ['Performance findings', '4,265'],
            ['Organizations with BYOK config', '79'],
            ['LLM providers represented', '5'],
            ['Distinct models in production use', '20+'],
            ['Codified review rules (KodyRules)', '7,276'],
            ['Organizations with codified rules', '610'],
          ].map(([k, v]) => (
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between border-b border-paper-300 py-2.5">
              <span class="text-ink-700">{k}</span>
              <span class="font-mono text-ink-900">{v}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ vi</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Out of scope</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          What is not included.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-ink-700 leading-[1.75] mt-5 space-y-2 list-none max-w-prose">
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">a.</span> Suggestions from Kodus self-hosted deployments. The data warehouse covers Cloud only.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">b.</span> Suggestions where delivery failed (failed_lines_mismatch, failed). Excluded from rate denominators because they never reached the developer.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">c.</span> Pull requests that never closed. Implementation status is only finalized at PR close.</li>
          <li class="pl-7 relative"><span class="absolute left-0 top-0 font-mono text-oxblood-500">d.</span> Pull requests from organizations that opted out of research. Reserved as policy. None currently.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="col-span-12 border-t border-paper-300"></div>

      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-3">
        <div class="tracked text-oxblood-500">§ vii</div>
        <div class="tracked text-ink-500 mt-2">Citation</div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
        <p class="font-display italic text-ink-900 leading-[1.35]" style="font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 2.2vw, 2rem);">
          How to cite.
        </p>
        <p class="font-mono text-sm bg-paper-200 border-l-2 border-oxblood-500 p-5 leading-relaxed mt-6 max-w-prose">
          State of AI Code Review (2026-Q2).<br />
          Research by Kodus.<br />
          https://stateofcodereview.com
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
